uments are clean.\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1456, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The city\", \"from\": 1401, \"to\": 1409}, {\"ngram\": \"the monuments\", \"from\": 1432, \"to\": 1445}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's going to be great.\\\"\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1481, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlike in previous Olympics, only two new permanent sports venues have been built for Paris 2024 in a deliberate change of strategy to make the Games cheaper and more \\\"sober\\\".\", \"from\": 1483, \"to\": 1658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1569, \"end\": 1579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.853368881899899e-30, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"previous Olympics\", \"from\": 1493, \"to\": 1510}, {\"ngram\": \"only two new permanent sports venues\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1548}, {\"ngram\": \"a deliberate change\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1602}, {\"ngram\": \"strategy\", \"from\": 1606, \"to\": 1614}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1623, \"to\": 1632}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An 8,000-seat arena that will host badminton and rhythmic gymnastics was inaugurated in a deprived part of northern Paris in February, while President Emmanuel Macron cut the ribbon at a new aquatics centre in a nearby suburb on April 4.\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1897, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1776, \"end\": 1781, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.262692189040068e-24, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1811, \"end\": 1826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron